  "important_notes": [
    "PartialComposer is the base class for lightweight Composer instances (global composer, no full load)",
    "Composer extends PartialComposer adding download, plugin, autoload, archive, and lock capabilities",
    "Factory::createComposer() is the single complex bootstrap method: loads config, creates all services, wires them into Composer/PartialComposer",
    "Factory decides at runtime whether to return Composer or PartialComposer based on $fullLoad boolean",
    "Installer uses a fluent builder pattern: all setters return self, then run() executes installation",
    "Installer::create(io, composer) is the intended entry point — extracts services from Composer object",
    "InstalledVersions is @final, all-static, designed to be copied into every installed project (runtime API)",
    "InstalledVersions uses ClassLoader::getRegisteredLoaders() to discover multiple vendor dirs in same process",
    "Compiler is build-time only — compiles composer.phar; uses Symfony Finder + PHP Phar extension",
    "Compiler explicitly excludes InstalledVersions.php and ClassLoader.php from whitespace stripping to preserve docblocks"
  ]
}
